Came here Wednesday cause Tank Noodle was closed.  Papaya Salad was fresh, the sliced pork and shrimp were well prepared. The herbs, fried garlic, and fried onion added a nice touch of flavor. The only downfall was that the sauce was a little too sweet and got to be a little overwhelming.  The Pho was a big let down. First they forgot the plate of bean sprouts and basil. There was no small side dish for hoisin and Sriracha. Most of the noodles were broken and the broth was heavy on star anise and five spice flavoring. It lacked the base of really good beef bone stock and it tasted like the packet of pho soup seasoning you can buy from the supermarket.  The Pork Chop and Pig Skin rice plate was decent, but nothing fancy or better than any other place.  Overall, I should have done more research and found something better in the area. Since I don't live in Illinois and don't come to this area often, it was a wasted meal and I wouldn't bother giving it another chance.
